<h1>Refund & Cancellation Policy</h1>
<p class="meta">Effective Date: [DATE]<br>Contact: <a href="mailto:rozhyperlocal@gmail.com">rozhyperlocal@gmail.com</a></p>

<div class="highlight">
  <p>Roz is a technology platform connecting customers with independent merchants. Refunds are the responsibility of the merchant. Roz's role is limited to facilitating communication between you and the merchant.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>1. Order Cancellation by Customer</h2>
<ul>
  <li>You may cancel an order <strong>before the merchant accepts it</strong> at no charge</li>
  <li>Once a merchant has accepted your order, cancellation is at the merchant's discretion</li>
  <li>Once delivery has been dispatched, orders cannot be cancelled</li>
  <li>To cancel, tap "Cancel Order" in the Orders section of the app</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>2. Order Cancellation by Merchant</h2>
<p>If a merchant cancels your order after acceptance (e.g. item out of stock), you will be notified immediately. For COD orders, no payment would have been collected so no refund is required. Roz will assist you in finding an alternative store where possible.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>3. Refund Eligibility</h2>
<p>You may be eligible for a refund if:</p>
<ul>
  <li>You received the wrong product</li>
  <li>You received a damaged or defective product</li>
  <li>Your order was not delivered despite being marked as delivered</li>
  <li>The product significantly differs from its description on the Platform</li>
</ul>
<p>Refund requests must be raised within <strong>24 hours</strong> of delivery by contacting rozhyperlocal@gmail.com with your order number and photos of the issue.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>4. Refund Process</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Roz will contact the merchant on your behalf within 24 hours of receiving your complaint</li>
  <li>The merchant has 48 hours to respond and confirm the refund</li>
  <li>If the merchant confirms the refund, it will be processed within 5-7 working days</li>
  <li>For COD orders, refunds are transferred via UPI to your registered mobile number</li>
  <li>If the merchant disputes your claim, Roz will review the evidence and make a final determination</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>5. Non-Refundable Items</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Roz platform service fee (10%) is non-refundable except where the order was not fulfilled at all</li>
  <li>Delivery fee is non-refundable once delivery has been dispatched</li>
  <li>Perishable goods (fresh produce, dairy, cooked food) are non-refundable unless delivered in a damaged or inedible condition</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>6. Lost or Damaged During Delivery</h2>
<p>If your order was lost or damaged during delivery:</p>
<ul>
  <li>If delivery insurance was enabled by the merchant, raise a claim directly with Borzo India at <a href="https://borzodelivery.com/in" style="color:#f5c842">borzodelivery.com</a> within 3 working days. Maximum coverage ₹50,000.</li>
  <li>If delivery insurance was not enabled, neither Roz nor the delivery partner accepts liability. This is disclosed at checkout before you place your order.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>7. Contact</h2>
<p>To raise a refund request or cancellation query:<br>
Email: <a href="mailto:rozhyperlocal@gmail.com">rozhyperlocal@gmail.com</a><br>
Include your order number and a description of the issue.</p>

